W. J. IMLACH, Appellant, v. Carl RUBENSTEIN, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit July 19, 1937. Walter H. Hodge, of Cordova, Alaska, and S. H. Kelleran, of Seattle, Wash., for appellant. Thomas M. Donohoe, of Cordova, Alaska, for appellee.

Before DENMAN, STEPHENS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and motion of appellant, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and -entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
